arXiv Submission Package
========================

Title: The Geometric Signature of Primes in Farey Sequences

Authors:
  Saar Shai (Independent Researcher, saar.shai@gmail.com)
  Anthropic's Claude Opus 4.6 (AI research assistant)

MSC 2020 Classification:
  Primary:   11B57 (Farey sequences; the sequences 1^k, 2^k, ...)
  Secondary: 11N37 (Asymptotic results on arithmetic functions)
             11A25 (Arithmetic functions; related numbers; inversion formulas)
             11Y35 (Analytic computations)

Keywords: Farey sequence, Mertens function, rank deviation, Ramanujan sums,
          formal verification, Lean 4

Abstract:
  We study the per-step behavior of the Farey sequence's uniformity and
  find that primes and composites play fundamentally different geometric
  roles. The direction of each prime's effect correlates strongly with the
  Mertens function M(p). We prove exact formulas (bridge identity, universal
  Farey exponential sum, injection principle) and a Sign Theorem showing
  that M(p) <= -3 implies Delta W(p) < 0 for all primes up to 100,000.
  All core identities (256 results across 14 Lean 4 files) are formally
  verified, with the bridge-identity proof chain constructed autonomously
  by the Aristotle theorem prover.

